{"Success":true,"Message":"Success","TotalRecord":1,"IsAuthFailure":false,"Data":[{"Tender_Id":99512056,"Bid_End_Date_Time":"07:05:2026 13:00","Bid_Opening_Date_Time":"<p>तकनीकि निविदा: 07.05.2026 15:00<br/>वित्तिय निविदा: Date and time will be notified later</p>","Department_Name":"Rajasthan State Seeds Corporation Limited","Emd_Instrument_Type":"No","Location":"Rajasthan","Products":"Transportaion work","State":"Rajasthan","Estimated_Cost":"0","EMD_Value":"2% of the estimated cost of the tender as per column number-4 of the tender invitation information<br>0.5% of the estimated cost of the tender in case of small scale industries of Rajasthan<br>1% of the estimated cost of the tender in case of sick industries other than small scale industries","Emd_Mode_Type":"DD / E-Grass Payment/Challan/ NEFT-RTGS","Pre_Bid_Meeting":"23:04:2026 15:00","Joint_Venture_OR_Consortium_OR_JV":"Yes","Performance_Bank_Guarantee":"5","Hard_Copy_Submission":"<p>Yes, the following documents must be submitted in hard copy:</p><br><ol><li>Demand draft for bid security amount.</li><li>Demand draft for tender fee.</li><li>Non-judicial stamp.</li></ol>","Levy_of_Penalty":"<p>If the authorized transport contractor does not make a truck available, a penalty of Rs 10,000/- per day will be charged. If this delay is due to unavoidable reasons where the transport contractor is not at fault, the concerned regional manager will forward recommendations for waiving the penalty to the headquarters after reviewing the reasons, and the final decision will be taken by the headquarters.</p><br><p>If the authorized transport contractor fails to deliver the goods to the destination within the specified time frame, the transport contractor will be charged a penalty of Rs 10,000/- per day to compensate for the losses incurred by the corporation.</p>","Affidavit_notarized_documents":"<p>Yes, the following documents are required to be submitted:</p><ul> <li>An affidavit on a stamp paper of Rs. 500/- stating that the firm has not been blacklisted/debarred in the last three years.</li> <li>Authority/Power of Attorney on a Rs. 100/- non-judicial stamp paper, or on letterhead with seal if the firm is a government entity.</li> <li>Declaration by the bidder on a Rs. 500/- non-judicial stamp paper</li></ul>","Mandatory_Pre_bid_Meeting":"No","Eligibility_Criteria":"<table><tr><th>Eligibility/Pre-Qualification Criteria</th><th>Details</th></tr><tr><td>Minimum Average Annual Turnover</td><td>The bidder's CA-certified average annual turnover (Annexure-F) should be equal to or more than the amount mentioned in Column 7 of the NIT. <br>If the firm's average turnover is less than the amount mentioned in Column 7 of the NIT for the relevant item, the bid will not be accepted. <br>If a bidder participates in more than one tender, the minimum average annual turnover must be equal to the sum of the required amounts for all submitted tenders.</td></tr><tr><td>Turnover Consideration</td><td>Turnover is to be considered for the past three financial years. (F.Y. 2022-23, 2023-24 and 2024-25).<br>If a firm has completed its accounts for the year 2025-26, the turnover of 2025-26 will also be valid.</td></tr><tr><td>Documents to prove Turnover</td><td>CA certified average annual turnover certificate (Annexure-F) and copies of ITR for the last 3 years.</td></tr><tr><td>Experience</td><td>The bidder must have experience of transporting goods in any one year out of the last five years (2021-22 to 2025-26) in a government office/public sector/PSU/corporation/board/undertaking (government-affiliated).<br>A work experience certificate and work order issued by the concerned office must be attached. The amount should be as per column 8 of the tender notice.<br>The amount of work experience must be equal to or greater than the amount mentioned in column 8 of the NIT.<br>If a bidder participates in more than one tender, the amount of work experience must be equal to the sum of the required amounts for all submitted tenders.</td></tr><tr><td>Blacklisting Declaration</td><td>The bidder must submit a self-declaration on non-judicial stamp paper of Rs. 500 that they have not been blacklisted/debarred by any department/organization in the last 3 years (Annexure-E).<br>If the firm is submitting a tender for more than one unit, separate stamp papers must be used for each unit. Submitting one stamp/affidavit for all tenders will result in rejection.</td></tr><tr><td>Mandatory Certifications/Registrations</td><td>GST Registration, PAN.</td></tr><tr><td>Legal Entity</td><td>The bidder can be an individual, private entity, government owned entity, a Joint Venture (JV) or consortium.</td></tr><tr><td>Other Declarations/Certificates</td><td><ul><li>Compliance with Code of Integrity and No Conflict of Interest (Annexure-A)</li><li>Declaration by the Bidder (Annexure-B)</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>Bid Security (EMD)</td><td>Bid security must be 2% of the estimated cost of the tender as per Column 4 of the tender notice.<br>For small scale industries of Rajasthan, it will be 0.5% of the estimated cost of the tender and for sick industries other than small scale industries, it will be 1% of the estimated cost.<br>The bid security should be submitted in the form of a DD drawn in favor of Rajasthan State Seeds Corporation Limited. It can also be submitted through banker's cheque, demand draft, bank guarantee or e-GRAS.<br>The bid security amount has to be submitted physically by the specified date and time at the corporation headquarters.</li></tr><tr><td>Additional Requirements</td><td><ul><li>The bidder must possess at least 2 trucks with a capacity of 9 tons.</li><li>If the trucks are not registered in the bidder's name, 1 truck should be in the name of the bidder or their family member (mother, father, wife, son, and daughter) and 1 truck should be taken on lease/agreement.</li><li>The lease deed and RC of the leased truck must be submitted with the tender.</li><li>The bidder must submit a copy of the MSME registration certificate if claiming exemptions applicable to MSMEs.</li></ul></td></tr></table>","Checklist":"1. Bid Security amount receipt/Demand Draft2. Tender Fee3. GST Registration Certificate4. Authority/Power of Attorney/Affidavit as per guidelines point number 36 on non-judicial stamp of Rs. 1005. The trucks owned by the tenderer, 2 trucks/one in own name and the truck taken on one lease, and the lease deed of the truck taken on lease should be attached.6. R.C. (Registration Certificate) of 2 trucks owned by the tenderer/one in his own name and one on lease (minimum 9 MT capacity)7. Photocopy of PAN card.8. CA certified average annual turnover certificate (Annexure-F)9. The tender form duly filled with the seal and signature of the tenderer on each page10. Affidavit on non-judicial stamp of Rs 500 that the firm is not blacklisted/debarred for last 3 years (Annexure-E)11. Declaration by bidder (500 Rs. on non-judicial stamp) (Annexure-B)12. Photocopy of Udyam Registration Certificate, if applicable."}],"StatusCode":200}